# V1 Functional MVP Rules (Django + PostgreSQL)
- Build a fully functional General Barter Marketplace MVP using four core apps: accounts, inventory, core_ledger, and trades.
- Implement an automatic 'Sign-up Bonus' token allocation inside the core_ledger application logic.
- Use an explicit Escrow state machine in the trades app to temporarily lock tokens during an active negotiation or delivery window.
- Ensure all location queries use standard latitude and longitude calculations to sort the main inventory feed by geographical proximity.
- Utilize a flexible Asset model with a PostgreSQL JSONB 'metadata' field to support varied item details while keeping the core schema generic.


"Claude, let's build the complete functional MVP for our multi-niche cashless marketplace using Django and PostgreSQL. This V1 will launch as a general barter network. Please scaffold the project into four clean, isolated apps: accounts, inventory, core_ledger, and trades. Implement user signup with a 100-token welcome credit, a location-aware asset feed using coordinates, and a trade negotiation workflow with an integrated escrow system to lock tokens. Ensure the inventory app uses a generic Asset model with a PostgreSQL JSONB field so the database remains fully future-proofed for our upcoming niches."
